			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I did my Innate regen and Run3 before going for 65, 130 aa's later I have accumulated many awesome and some silly aa's...
<br />
I mainly group, solo rarely and usually only when farming in FG or PoI for tradeskills... so here imo are the best aa's to get asap...
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Pet Discipline</span>
<br />
go for Pet Disc IMMEDIATELY!  i noticed some people poo poo'ing this awesome aa and here's why it's useful... 
<br />

<br />
1) no more slamming the "back off" when you need to switch targets in a pinch, hit 'pet hold' 'pet back off (1x)' and resassist... boom done, no hassle and it's immediate...
<br />

<br />
2) makes Mages a viable puller!  I use pet hold to pull constantly, and allows me to single pull mobs that most other's cant w/o a pacify... why???
<br />
cuz pets do NOT get the same agro as PC's... so pick yer mob... pet attack, he runs up, smacks em, hit pet hold and back he comes Along w/ Mr. monster!
<br />

<br />
3) the mob is being pushed the wrong direction! pet hold, move, reassist, it's absolutely painless now.
<br />

<br />
4) RAIDS!  when you come to mobs that use AoE's this is a MUST!  since you must wait for your MT to call an engage and you've usually already gotten hit by an AE at that point, unless your pet is on hold he WILL attack, this makes YOU a liability!  it could place you on rampage or have other serious consequences!  until Pet Hold in my guild we did not allow pets on raids that had a target that AE'd, now it's a non issue 
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Suspend Minion</span>
<br />
omfg people this is still THE coolest thing since sliced bread!  I use this one on a daily basis in a variety of situations
<br />

<br />
1) solo'ing: have pet fully buffed and geared on suspend in case yer 1st pet goes down, boom quick cast yer saved!
<br />

<br />
2) invis!  you can suspsend and invis wherever needed, or use Eye of Tallon *which makes you invisible* for those times when your Clay Bracelet Eye of Zomm wont last long enuf
<br />

<br />
3) coth will destroy the unsummoned pet, but not the suspended one!
<br />

<br />
4) perfect for when you want to charm, like in BoT or Tak! place your normal pet on suspend and grab yerself a elemental or summoned greater defender, incase you lose your charmed mob, you still have yer faithful one on immediate standby
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Mend Companion and Hastened Mending</span>
<br />
holy cow... mana free instant heal for 2146, Imp healing does not affect this AA but still is awesome in a pinch and with only a 9 min refresh is well worth 11 aa.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Innate Enlightenment and Planar Power</span>
<br />
I cannot stress enuf how awesome having 355 (soon 380) Intelligence is, once i maxed these out i started dropping gear that didn't have mana (such as my grimling skin mask) and w/in a few days had increased my mana pool by 700pts, now at 5600+ w/o any elemental  or GoD gear.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">SCM3 and FoM3</span>
<br />
this is a route I chose to go, and honestly it's awesome, at FoM2 my max crit ever is 4600 w/ Firebolt of Tallon and using Imp Dmg 4 and Call of the Muse, w/o bard buff max seems 4400 but I do this on a consistent basis.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Mental Clarity 3</span>
<br />
Some people seem to think this isn't worth it but imo it is indeed, it gives additional 3 mana regen for less then Water Elemental form 3 and is always available, perfect for those who can't max out worn FT15 immediately.
<br />

<br />
I'm still playing w/ the GoD ones, and although I want Pet Affinity for the ability, I dont raid enough at this point to make it worth the 20aa cost.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=608950" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.divinesilence.shattering.us/sigs/thayetsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
