<br />
I am particularly interested in why you have ranked a bugged aa (Advanced Pet Discipline) so high in the recommended path. It will only take a pet breaking a mez one time to open a whole can of worms. Even had this not been bugged Im not sure it deserves this high a place for a raid mage.
<br />
Also interested to note that you ranked Persistant Minion so high. What does that bring to a raid mage that is so good it deserves to be before crits and subtelty?
<br />

<br />
My personal philosophy is that the raid mage should be doing maximum damage without getting summoned and these two aa to me seem to deserve a much lower spot in the raid mage progression. 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, maybe im stupid and missing something here so please enlighten me on these points.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
